Eleven people were left injured after the taxi they were travelling
in overturned on Madadeni Road in Newcastle on Thursday morning. Craig Botha, spokesperson for Kwazulu Private Ambulance Service, said when emergency services arrived at the scene,
they found that a taxi had lost control and overturned. He said 11 people had suffered injuries ranging from minor
to serious and were taken to hospital. In another accident, Botha said four people were seriously
injured when two cars collided on the R102 near Canefields in KwaZulu-Natal on
Wednesday night.